{{Infobox instrument | name = Trīdeksnis | image = | image_size = | caption = | background = percussion | names = Trīdeksnis, trīdēkslis, trīdēksnis, strīdēkslis, trīzdeksnis, strīzdeklis, strīzdiķis, ztrīzdiķis, trideksnis, tridēksnis, trijdeksnis, trumulis, trumulītis, trumuls, trumele, trumelis, trumēliņš, čakans, čokans, čokens, čakārnis, čagana<ref name="Systematics"/> | classification = [[Percussion instrument]], [[idiophone]] | hornbostel_sachs = 112.112 | hornbostel_sachs_desc = Stick rattle | inventors = [[Folk instrument]] | developed = | timbre = | volume = | attack = | decay = | range = | pitch = | related = | musicians = | builders = }}
'''Trīdeksnis''' (also known as '''trīdēkslis''', '''trīdēksnis''', '''strīdēkslis''' etc<ref name="Systematics">{{Cite web |title= Systematics of Latvian musical instruments |first= Valdis |last= Muktupāvels |authorlink=Valdis Muktupāvels |year= 1999 |publisher= Latvijas Mākslas augstskolu asociācija |url= http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:o1Mp9A3Tq-0J:www3.acadlib.lv/greydoc/Muktupavela_disertacija/disertacija.doc |language=Latvian |access-date=December 10, 2012 |pages=62–63 |quote=Trīdeksnis (Mazzalve Z; Ikšķile V; Embūte K), šāds nosaukums minēts arī Ulmaņa vārdnīcā, trīdēkslis (Alsunga K), trīdēksnis, strīdēkslis, trīzdeksnis, strīzdeklis, strīzdiķis (Brukna Z), ztrīzdiķis, trideksnis, tridēksnis (Nīca K), trijdeksnis (Naudīte Z).}}</ref>) is a Latvian [[percussion instrument]]. It consists of a short wooden handle running through three increasing width tiers of flat horizontal discs, with small triangular metal [[Rattle (percussion beater)|rattles]] hanging off the edges of the disks. The trīdeksnis is used by shaking it like a rattle or hitting the handle against the palm, causing metal discs to jingle.<ref>{{cite web |first=Amanda |last=Jātniece |title=A primer on Latvian folk instruments |url=http://latviansonline.com/a-primer-on-latvian-folk-instruments/ |accessdate=September 8, 2012 |website=Latvians Online |date=July 16, 2001}}</ref>
In [[NBC]] series [[Community (TV series)|''Community'']], the trīdeksnis is played during a [[Latvia]]n independence day parade in episode [[Conspiracy Theories and Interior Design]].
