'''Alvaro VIII''' (Mvemba a Mpanzu), of the [[House of Kinlaza]], was king of the [[Kingdom of Congo]], from 1666 to 1669.

==Biography==
Alvaro VIII was elevated to the throne by [[Paulo da Silva, Count of Soyo]], who marched on [[M'banza-Kongo|São Salvador]] and killed his predecessor, [[Álvaro VII of Kongo|King Alvaro VII]].

In 1667, he sent his ambassador, Anastasius, to [[Luanda]] ([[Angola]]), to negotiate a treaty that ceded to the Portugueses the right to exploit the mines of Congo, located in the provinces of [[Mbamba]] and [[Mpemba]]. Theodosius, Duke of Mbamba, bowed to the king's decision, but Peter, Duke of Mbemba, refused.

Leading a small army, Peter attacked Mbamba, killed Theodosius and then invaded the kingdom's capital, [[M'banza-Kongo|São Salvador]], killing Alvaro VIII and proclaimed himself king under the name of [[Pedro III of Kongo|Peter III]].

